The paper deals with learning algorithms and low-rank matrix/tensor factorizations, which are topics commonly studied in the machine learning and data science communities. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are likely categories. The use of random projections and compressed sensing techniques suggests that cs.IT (Information Theory) may also be relevant. The paper also discusses the preservation of certain solutions of non-convex, NP-Hard problems, which could fall under cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
